parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Light Control Module can cause the headlights to turn off without warning, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights turn off while driving
headlights do not turn back on after switching the light switch on and off
park lights work normally
bright lights work when manually operated
windshield wipers only work on high speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rusting and cracked wheels can lead to wheel failure, causing loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rusting or corrosion on the wheels
visible clean metal on the wheel surface
wheel finish disappearing
cracked wheels
air leaks
and flat tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the right front brake hose can cause a loss of power brake assist, leading to increased stopping distances and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Loss of power brake assist
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal travels further than usual
vehicle takes longer to stop
brake warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump and filter can cause the vehicle to hesitate, stall, and lack power, which can lead to accidents, especially in high-stress situations such as police pursuits.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates
stalls
or lacks power
especially during acceleration or when carrying heavy loads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the vehicle continues to accelerate despite applying the brake
the vehicle does not respond to brake input
the accelerator pedal becomes stuck or unresponsive.
